Parliament, Tuesday 11 May 2021 – Deputy President Mr David Mabuza will answer questions for oral replies in the National Assembly and Economic Cluster 4F Ministers will be in the National Council of Provinces (NCOP), tomorrow, Wednesday 12 May.
	
	Parliament uses a range of instruments to hold the Executive accountable, including putting questions to the Deputy President and Cabinet Ministers. Section 92(2) of the Constitution stipulates that Cabinet Members are collectively and individually accountable to Parliament for the exercise of powers and performance of their functions.
	
	For the list of questions to the Deputy President, please click:
	https://www.parliament.gov.za/storage/app/media/Docs/quest_pap/6cc3e8f4-80c3-48c8-8c35-4058328bbb28.pdf
	
	Details of the NA hybrid sitting are as follows:
	
	Date: Wednesday 12 May 2021
	Time: 14.00
	Venue: National Assembly Chamber and virtual platform
	
	For the list of questions to Economic Cluster please click:
	https://www.parliament.gov.za/storage/app/media/Docs/quest_pap/68234e4a-5068-4c39-a177-52c8d03faef9.pdf
	
	Details of the NCOP plenary are as follows:
	
	Date: Wednesday 12 May 2021
	 Time: 14:00
	 Venue: NCOP Chamber and virtual platforms
	
	Important to note:
	
	Members of the media who wish to physically attend the NA and NCOP Hybrid Sittings tomorrow should send their details (Full name, name of the media house, and ID or passport number) to Mlindi Mpindi on email: mmpindi@parliament.gov.za.
	
	Members of the media who wish to cover virtual Parliamentary Committee Meetings should forward their contact details to Mlindi Mpindi on mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared. Journalists must forward their requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the proceedings live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via the live stream on Parliament’s YouTube channel, Facebook and Twitter pages. Please see links below.
	
	You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
